# Auto detect text files and perform LF normalization
* text=auto

# Append-only audit log: every lane appends run records, so parallel branches
# collide at EOF on merge. `merge=union` keeps BOTH sides' added lines instead
# of raising a conflict (records are independent; order/duplication is tolerable
# for an audit trail). Re-derive a sorted view downstream if ever needed.
#
# The run log is sharded into per-lane files under docs/agent-logs/runs/ (T-046).
# `merge=union` here auto-resolves LOCAL rebase/merge collisions on a shared shard
# (e.g. the dated `*-main.jsonl` lane). NOTE: this is a complement to — not a
# replacement for — the T-046 sharding: GitHub does NOT run merge drivers
# server-side, so sharding remains what prevents server-side PR conflicts; this
# attribute only helps merges/rebases performed locally. The consolidated
# agent-runs.jsonl is a gitignored derived view (T-046), so it needs no attribute.
docs/agent-logs/runs/*.jsonl merge=union
